6 An Act relating to open pasture roads; amending
Section 1, Chapter 191, O.S.L. 2024 (4 O.S. Supp.
7 2025, Section 116), which relates to open pasture
road designations; modifying definition; modifying
8 requirements for designation of an open pasture road;
removing certain time limitation; granting certain
9 authority to boards of county commissioners; updating
statutory language; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 191, O.S.L.
15 2024 (4 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 116), is amended to read as
16 follows:
17 Section 116. A. As used in this section:
18 1. “Cattle crossing signage” means a sign in a twenty-four (24)
19 inch twenty-four-inch diamond shape that depicts a black cow graphic
20 on a yellow background; and
21 2. “Open pasture road” means a road maintained by a county;
22 where the land on both sides of the road is owned or leased by the
23 same owner or lessee; and a such roadway is without fencing.
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 2112 Page 1

1 B. Any public road, as defined in Section 232 of Title 69 of
2 the Oklahoma Statutes, in whole or in part, that is maintained by a
3 county and that meets the following conditions by November 1, 2025,
4 shall be designated as an open pasture road:
5 1. Cattle guards have been installed at the access points of
6 such road or part thereof; and
7 2. The land on either side of the road or part thereof to be
8 designated is owned by a single party; and
9 3. There is no fencing erected on such land on either side of
10 the road Cattle are allowed to be unrestrained or to run at large
11 through such roads.
12 It shall be the responsibility of the property owner to notify
13 the board of county commissioners that the roadway is eligible to be
14 designated as an open pasture road. Such notification shall state
15 the proposed action and clearly show on a map the location and
16 terminals of the road. The map shall also demonstrate that the
17 property where the road is located belongs to the property owner
18 requesting such designation.
19 C. The board of county commissioners shall cause the erection
20 of cattle crossing signage at the terminals of the open pasture
21 road. The cost associated with such signage shall be provided by
22 the property owner requesting such designation.
23 D. Neither the property owner nor the owner of livestock that
24 are on property where an open pasture road is located shall be
ENGR. S. B. NO. 2112 Page 2

1 liab le for damages to any motor vehicle or occupants thereof caused
2 by collision with livestock on a designated open pasture road. If
3 property is damaged, the driver of the motor vehicle shall be liable
4 for such damages.
5 E. Only a public road meeting the requirements of subsection B
6 of this section on November 1, 2025, may be designated as an open
7 pasture road. After such date, even if conditions on a property
8 change to meet the requirements of subsection B of this section,
9 such property may not be designated as The board of county
10 commissioners shall have authority to designate an open pasture
11 road.
12 F. Once annually, the owner of a property where an open pasture
13 road is located shall provide notice to the board of county
14 commissioners demonstrating that the property continues to meet the
15 requirements of subsection B of this section. Such notice shall
16 also include an indication that the property owner desires such
17 designation to continue. If such property owner indicates that they
18 the owner no longer desire desires for such designation to continue,
19 or if the notice demonstrates that the property no longer meets any
20 of the conditions required by subsection B of this section, the road
21 shall lose the designation and the owner of such property shall have
22 thirty (30) days after the board of county commissioners receives
23 such notice to ensure any livestock on the property are fenced out
24 of the roadway.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 2112 Page 3

1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
